node.text:
Virginia Union University graduate Ben Wallace just recently became the first undrafted player to be selected for the Naismith Hall of Fame.

Facts about Ben Wallace from the VUU website :
“During his 16-year NBA career, Wallace earned the NBA's Defensive Player of the Year award four times (2002, 2003, 2005 and 2006), all with the Detroit Pistons. He was also the defensive anchor for the 2004 "Goin' to Work" championship team. Wallace spent nine seasons with the organization, from 2002-06 and from 2009-12.

In 1,088 career games, he averaged 5.7 points, 9.6 rebounds, 1.3 steals and two blocks in 29.5 minutes per game with Washington, Orlando, Detroit, Chicago and Cleveland.”

📷 @ciaasports

node.text:
Verified
"It’s just an honor to join the National Football League," - Maia Chaka

Maia Chaka has been added to the NFL roster of game officials for the 2021 season, making her the first Black woman ever named to the NFL's officiating staff.

Chaka is a graduate of Norfolk State University, where she earned her bachelor's in education in 2006 before embarking on her teaching and officiating careers.

Chaka is the second-ever female NFL referee. Sarah Thomas was hired as the first full-time female official in NFL in 2015. In February, she became the first woman to officiate in a Super Bowl.

node.text:
Shoutout to @alaskaair ! 
“We are proud to be the first airline to join the Historically Black Colleges and Universities (HBCU) Partnership Challenge. It is an effort put forth by the bipartisan Congressional HBCU Caucus to promote greater engagement and support between private companies and HBCUs.
 
We recently established commitments and specific goals to increase BIPOC representation in leadership, continue to cultivate an inclusive culture, and to lead publicly by supporting education on the path to equity. Learn more at the link in our bio.”

node.text:
Just a reminder that whatever you are going through in life , know that your life can change in a matter of seconds, literally!! 

Do you all remember when college student Anok Yai was spotted in 2017 at Howard University’s homecoming from a photo @thesunk took of her? She has come along way since that photo including magazine covers, modeling agency, and pictured on the right, at the Met Gala yesterday 

What a message from @historicallyblacksince ! 🔥
